caption: Great food. Nice place to eat.
Consistently good quality from this place, which has been a go-to for years. The staff is always friendly and helpful.
Their Wonton soup is the best I’ve had.
Pretty good Chinese food - nothing fancy but it's a good value for what you are paying.  Solid go to Chinese food.
Everything feels fresh and delicious! The ramen was very top notch! Highly recommend.
Incredible food at a good price. Staff is so nice and polite. Stopped by while on a walk one day and we’ll definitely be back again and again!

Great food option in the Prospect Heights area! The restaurant is clean, food is good, and staff are extremely friendly! People are constantly coming and going for takeout with a few people sitting in the dining room. The ramen is excellent and so is the sushi!
The Spicy Tonkatsu Ramen is delicious. I'd definitely go back.
Was here for first time and don’t like it at all. Food not tasty. They need to change a chef. Not recommended.

One of my favorite local spots and the best Asian food I know around the neighborhood. The dumplings, General Tso’s chicken, ramen soup and bubble tea are all excellent. Sushi is also fresh and always delicious. Will be back for more!

This place is definitely my go to place when it comes to good pokey bowls fish is always fresh fruits and vegetables are amazing super juicy and you feel the freshness in every bite the staff are super friendly and very welcoming I really look forward to every visit. Al the place is very clean 🧼 Love this place!!

Someone Order me food from there once so I decided to try it myself I ordered the poke bowl i got a spoonful of rice mango sauce cucumbers and one shrimp chop in little pieces for $12:26 i was very disappointed.please be aware....,
I'm not a big eater, but I needed two dinners to feel full
Cozy place and great food with good prices.

I am amazed that this place is not always crowded... it’s the best kept secret in the neighborhood. This place is amazing. I love that it is family owned. They are wonderful people. The chefs are incredible, the food is delicious. It is the best restaurant in the neighborhood. I am vegetarian and they have amazing food for us. I love them! I ate there again and had the most amazing delicious food. They have added new recipes to their menu. I am grateful to have found this restaurant, they never disappoint. It is a secret treasure! It may be the best restaurant in all of NYC!

(delivery) - It's ok. Egg rolls are HUGE, thick crispy shell. Sushi - the sweet potato was under cooked (harder bite), the rice could have a little more cook-time but acceptable.  Geyoza (steamed) could be made a little tighter (rips before biting). Got potential, but currently it's just OK.

The food looked good but the taste didn't match. I usually like this type of shrimp but i was not feeling it at all on top of that the sauce that was given didnt taste good with it. The soup was the worse i tasted it and left it alone. The only decent thing was the bubble tea. However the server was nice and I like how the food was served on a small skillet pan

They have a new poke bowl menu! For 9.55 you could get a choice of protein,  3 mixins and unlimited toppings and sauces. It is made straight at the sushi bar, so all of the fish was nice and fresh. The chicken which I also ordered were grilled to order. Definitely will be back to try it with the bubble tea next time.

Clean environment, prompt and friendly service... and the food!!!! Large portions, reasonable prices and absolutely fantastic taste! Our new favorite restaurant! Street parking in Brooklyn though - be warned.
Food is delicious!!! I love it.
A big variety of sushi on the menu. Very affordable food and great service!!!!
I love them. They always get it right with us. I have much respect and love for them.

I usually order through the phone for either pickup or delivery and each time the customer service gets worst and worst . If I could I will give the a 0 . Get a new person on the phone because the one you have is clearly not working for you
General Tao chicken and scallion pancake both taste amazing and the delivery’s really fast

We haven't been here for a few months, the decoration style in the restaurant has changed, it looks very beautiful, we still order pork dumplings and lunch bento boxes, there’s a new topping, pudding in the bubble tea,I like it very much, pudding is very smooth
AMAZINGGG FOOOOD!! Very Fast Delivery and I live pretty far :)
The restaurant is always very comfortable and quiet.  Amazing food.

The best Asian fusion place around Prospect Park! My roommates and I order take out at least once a week (if not way more) and they never disappoint! Amazing values on their combination plates - chicken dishes always cooked to perfection, fresh veggies, delicious dumplings! I’m gonna stay in Prospect Heights just so tgis restaurant is always close by!
Ordered here a few times for takeout and dined her a few times too. All I have to say is fast food, great service and beautiful decorations inside the restaurant.
Fast delivery, great food and friendly staff. Definitely recommend.
The volcano roll is great! You also have to have their shrimp teriyaki bento..it's very good!
Good food and reasonable prices
This place is awesome! Open a little later than the other restaurants in the area, which is nice. The food is great and the customer service is amazing!
I work in the neighborhood and have eaten here many times. The atmosphere is nice. They are consistently good, and always very friendly. Thank you for so many good meals here!!

DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE. Terrible costumer service and pricer than other Asian establishments near by. Delivery was over an hour and a half just to be delivered to the wrong location(mind you I live only two blocks away). Only to get a sorry and tried not to give a discount.

Had the lunch bento box. Fantastic portion for the price. For $10.75, you get a miso soup, green salad with ginger dressing, a spring roll, a California roll, white or brown rice and one of the entree options. I had the sesame chicken. Sauce was pretty sweet, but the chicken is white meat, the breading was not excessive like it sometimes can be. Overall, really good food and nice atmosphere. Will return if I'm in this area again.
Great combo plates. Love the Kung Pao chicken and General Tso's. Excellent egg rolls too!
I looooove the sushi from this place!!
Food was excellent! Service was great!

Order from here. They do not disappoint. Order the egg rolls. So crisp and crunchy, but not enough to where the egg rolls crumbles apart. Moo Shoo Pork. Fried Rice. Lo Mein. It’s fire for sure. Like, they could mess up a future order and I’d still continue ordering from here lol.
Great neighborhood spot. Tasty food and quick service.
I like this General Tso’s chicken, and the skin of the dumpling is very thin. I like it very much. The taste of pearl milk tea is very authentic.

Great place! Nice atmosphere and very friendly staff. Their Thai curry is amazing with the right balance between a little spice and the sweet coconut milk. The fried dumplings and General Tso’s Chicken is also delicious. They also serve iced and warm bubble tea in many different flavors. Will definitely be back!

Great variety of good tasting Asian food, mainly Japanese and Chinese cuisine.  There were 18 of us.  We made a reservation for luncheon and everything was nicely set up when we arrived.  Service was attentive; all orders arrived after a very short wait.  Most of us ordered the Bento box (Choice of Japanese, Chinese or Vegetarian entree) which comes with soup, salad, spring roll, rice and condiments like sliced ginger and wasabi for those who ordered Japanese.  The bento box is great value at $10.50.  Mango bubble tea $2.00 and mango sticky rice dessert extra $2.50 extra.

Took a lunch special "to go" from there once. The environment is good. They have a spacious waiting room. Staff is extremely friendly. The food is good. They have bubble tea (which is hard to find in that area).

I ordered a green Thai curry and bubble tea for delivery. The Thai curry was not a soup base like in any other place, thy served it with a thick white sauce. When I called to say they made a mistake, she insisted that their Thai curry is not served as soup but as a rice dish. The bubble tea tasted like fish and when we complained they started yelling at us. Never again!
Cool Sushi spot... Date night
Dinner special deals are reasonably priced. The staff is very friendly. The sushi rolls are fresh and super tasty.

As of July 14th, this restaurant is known as: Ke Lai Le Awesome place! Had the pineapple fried rice with pork, vegetarian sushi, and banana fried green tea ice cream. All were phenomenal! Service was excellent and atmosphere was peaceful and soothing. They allowed us to bring in our own alcohol from outside and  uncorked the bottle for us. Easily one of the best Asian cuisine destinations I've ever been to. Highly recommended!
Nice  waiters and great food.
Has a great atmosphere and the food there is also great
Always a good get away for nice food quiet atmosphere
Take out menu is much larger than at a table. MAKES NO SENSE!!! Like the number of things avaible is decreased immensly
Amazing place  :) I love the Shrimp Shumai
A great variety of tasty Asian fusion options. Bubble tea is great. Prices are reasonable. Highly suggest fried pork gyoza
Good food , nice portions, reasonable prices.
Excellent to dine or take out !
Medicore sushi. Very rude service and rude delievery. The delievery guy started yelling at me in chinese because he didnt like his tip. But the food is edible.
Great food, service as cold as ice tea.
(Translated by Google) Sheet! Terrible!  (Original) Blech!  Terrible!
Pad Thai is delicious
AWWWW S**T, DUMPLINGS MUTHER ****ER, DO YOU LIVE THEM?  ***K YES YOU DO.  GET SOME GOD ***** DUMPLINGS ***** ****.
Excellent sushi for a great price, get the spicy tuna
Best of Japanese & Chinese. Well run. Good prices. Great sake!
Good cheap chinese food - get the dumplings!

I use Colala for delivery.  They're the best delivery Chinese food in my area of Crown Heights.  They are extremely prompt, and the food is always fresh and hot.  I have not tried their Japanese menu yet but it looks promising.  Try the wontons.
